A [[Electromagnetic pulse/Legends|magnetic-pulse]] weapon similar in design to the handheld [[Electromagnetic pulse grenade/Legends|EMP grenade]], '''droid busters''', also called '''magpulse busters''', were concussion-feedback missiles equipped on [[Low Altitude Assault Transport/infantry/Legends|LAAT/is]] near the end of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]]. They detonated five meters above the ground, and could neutralize every [[Battle droid/Legends|battle droid]] within a fifty-meter radius.

Several droid buster missiles were utilized in the opening stages of the [[Battle of Murkhana (Clone Wars)|Battle of Murkhana]], which took place in the last days of the Clone Wars. They cleared the beachhead and drop zone of numerous [[B1-series battle droid/Legends|B1]] and [[B2-series super battle droid/Legends|B2]] battle droids and even a couple of [[IG-227 Hailfire-class droid tank/Legends|''Hailfire'']] units, allowing the clones under the command of [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Roan Shryne]] to land in relative safety.

